<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0">
    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>Memorandum by the Acting Secretary of
                            State to President Truman</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1946v11</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d321</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">321</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1946-08-09T00:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1946-08-09T23:59:59-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-08-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-08-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="321" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d321">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">824.01/8–946</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss> to President <persName type="to">Truman</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-08-09">August 9,
                            1946</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The new government in Bolivia, according to reports received from Ambassador
                    Flack, has now demonstrated its ability to maintain order, and has fully
                    expressed its intention to meet all international commitments. Six other
                    American republics, including Bolivia’s immediate neighbors, Peru and Chile,
                    have already recognized the new government, and our Ambassador yesterday
                    telegraphed that he felt “strongly that recognition by the United States is very
                    important at this stage and should now be extended as soon as possible.”<note n="57" xml:id="d321fn57">The following notation appears in the margin:
                        “Approved 8/9/46 Harry Truman.”</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dean Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
